üîé Analytical Framework

Each side must be assessed against these dimensions:
	1.	Current Combat Power & Force Projection (land, sea, air, cyber, space).
	2.	Logistics & Sustainment Capabilities (industrial capacity, global basing, supply chains).
	3.	Historical Combat Experience & Military Culture.
	4.	Command & Control Structures (interoperability, joint operations, unity of command).
	5.	Information Warfare & Propaganda (psychological ops, media control, disinformation).
	6.	Intelligence, Surveillance, Reconnaissance (ISR) capabilities.
	7.	Cyber Warfare (attack and defense infrastructures).
	8.	Financial & Economic Warfare (sanctions, blockades, currency shocks, industrial mobilization).
	9.	Space Domain (satellites, GPS, comms, surveillance, anti-satellite warfare).
	10.	Civil Defense & Homeland Resilience (population protection, continuity of government).
	11.	Leadership & Doctrine Adaptability (specific military/political leaders, decision-making styles).
	12.	Role of Non-State Actors (PMCs, militias, insurgencies, terrorist networks, corporations).
	13.	Environmental & Geographic Factors (terrain, climate, chokepoints, energy access).
	14.	Global Interdependencies (trade networks, energy flows, food security).
	15.	Adherence to or Violations of LOAC (impact on legitimacy, alliances, and morale).

