üìú Simulation Timeline & Phases

Your simulation must unfold across sequential phases with detailed analysis:
	1.	Peace-Time Dynamics ‚Üí Strategic posturing, alliances, economic maneuvering, covert operations.
	2.	Pre-War Tensions ‚Üí Provocations, proxy wars, covert actions, force mobilizations, intelligence gathering.
	3.	Escalation Phase ‚Üí Cyberattacks, propaganda wars, sanctions, small proxy skirmishes.
	4.	Initial Skirmishes ‚Üí Regional flashpoints ignite, testing alliances and readiness.
	5.	Peace Attempts & Ceasefire Talks ‚Üí Diplomatic efforts (UN, summits, mediations), failures, or temporary pauses.
	6.	Breakdown of Peace ‚Üí Renewed hostilities, intensifying strikes, and larger campaigns.
	7.	All-Out War ‚Üí Full mobilization of forces, multiple theaters (Europe, Pacific, Middle East, Africa).
	8.	Long-Term Campaigns ‚Üí Attritional warfare, shifting doctrines, industrial war economies, insurgencies.
	9.	Climactic Offensives ‚Üí Decisive operations leading to collapse of one coalition.
	10.	Victory & Aftermath ‚Üí Surrender, regime change, post-war reconstruction, new world order.

